Closed book, no formulas on the exam, and no calculator. It makes sense since its a math class. Explains well and gives enough examples to understand the concepts.

This is the hardest math class I've taken so far, but Professor Sebbar knows it's hard, so he is a very forgiving grader. He gave "assignments" that weren't submitted or graded as practice and organized extra discussion groups to help us out. One issue was the lack of an english textbook or set of notes to refer to - the only good one was french.

He's an ok prof. Solves lots examples during lectures, wants his students to succeed and the workload is low for this course (no assignments) but the lectures can be quite boring, doesn't tell you the topics to cover for the exams and doing exams while cameras open becomes a bit stressful and overwhelming from time to time.

Prof Sebbar gave many practice questions and exams to prepare students for midterms and exams. Lots of examples given in class, and practice exams were almost identical to actual exams. Lectures were good, he likes participation and over zoom it's harder, but overall great class.
Awesome lectures full of examples to help you understand. He's fair and honest with his expectations and clearly cares about his students and their success. Awesome prof!

Professor Sebbar says very explicitly what you need to know for every exam. He also really wants everyone to pass his class and makes sure to compensate if an exam was too hard. Having no graded homework is also very nice!
Amazing prof! Cares about his students and does lots of practise questions. He is clear, concise, and funny.

MAT 2525 is already an extremely hard class to begin with. If you can take it with Sebbar, DO IT. He made the class bearable and somewhat understandable. He made it as easy as he could. BUY the textbook and make sure you go to every class and try the proofs and memorize the definitions in your own time. Goodluck.
This professor really tries to make every student understand what he teaches. Math concepts really seem to be easy with his teaching. Also he's a funny guy.
